---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Help & Safety" description="How Denver Social works — for attendees and organizers — and the safety rules that keep it good.">
  <div class="hp-wrap">
    <header class="hp-header">
      <h1>Help & Safety</h1>
      <p class="hp-sub">Short answers for attendees and organizers, and the rules that keep things good. <a href="/contact">Contact us</a> if something's missing.</p>
    </header>

    <nav class="hp-toc" aria-label="Quick jump">
      <a href="#transparency">🪟 Transparency</a>
      <a href="#why-not">🤔 Why not __?</a>
      <a href="#attendees">🎟 Attendees</a>
      <a href="#groups">👥 Groups</a>
      <a href="#organizers">🎤 Organizers</a>
      <a href="#privacy">🔒 Privacy</a>
      <a href="#reporting">🚩 Reporting</a>
      <a href="#safety">🛡 Safety & terms</a>
    </nav>

    <section class="hp-sec" id="transparency">
      <h2>Transparency</h2>
      <p class="hp-section-lede">Everything we do, in plain English. No secrets, no fine print.</p>

      <div class="hp-grid">
        <div class="hp-box hp-box-ok">
          <div class="hp-box-head">
            <span class="hp-box-emoji">📦</span>
            <strong>What we collect</strong>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Your name + email (to run your account)</li>
            <li>Neighborhood (so events feel local)</li>
            <li>RSVPs + check-ins (so you remember what you went to)</li>
            <li>Reddit/Discord username + karma (if you linked them)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="hp-box hp-box-no">
          <div class="hp-box-head">
            <span class="hp-box-emoji">🚫</span>
            <strong>What we don't do</strong>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>No ads, ever</li>
            <li>No selling your data — to anyone</li>
            <li>No algorithm deciding what you see</li>
            <li>No engagement tricks, push notification spam, or dark patterns</li>
            <li>No paywall, no premium tier, no upsell</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="hp-box">
          <div class="hp-box-head">
            <span class="hp-box-emoji">💸</span>
            <strong>What it costs to run</strong>
          </div>
          <p>Depends on usage. The bill scales with how much email we send, how much database storage we use, and how many people are on the site. Today it's small because we're small — paid out of pocket by Seth. If costs ever get significant, we'll publish the actual numbers here.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Cloudflare Workers + D1 + KV — hosting + database</li>
            <li>Resend — RSVP confirmations + reminder emails</li>
            <li>No investors, no revenue, no plan to take any</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="hp-box">
          <div class="hp-box-head">
            <span class="hp-box-emoji">👤</span>
            <strong>Who runs it</strong>
          </div>
          <p>Seth Tharpe, a local. Email <a href="mailto:stharpe98@gmail.com">stharpe98@gmail.com</a> or DM <code>@godtminilegs</code> on Discord. No team, no company — yet.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="hp-box">
          <div class="hp-box-head">
            <span class="hp-box-emoji">⚖️</span>
            <strong>How decisions get made</strong>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Admins approve partner perks before they go live</li>
            <li>Reports get reviewed within ~48 hours</li>
            <li>Account removals happen when someone violates <a href="#safety">the rules</a> — usually after one warning</li>
            <li>Anything bigger (new features, policy changes): announced in Discord first</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="hp-box">
          <div class="hp-box-head">
            <span class="hp-box-emoji">📂</span>
            <strong>Your data is yours</strong>
          </div>
          <p>You can delete your account anytime from <a href="/profile">/profile</a> — it wipes your record and all your RSVPs. Want a copy of your data first? Email Seth.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="hp-sec" id="why-not">
      <h2>Why not just use ___?</h2>
      <p class="hp-why-intro">Honest answers. We don't think any of these are bad — they just solve a different problem.</p>

      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Why not Meetup?</summary>
        <p>Meetup charges organizers $20–30/month per group and gates the experience behind paywalls. It feels corporate, the app pushes ads, and small groups end up paying real money to host free events. Denver Social is free for everyone — organizers and attendees. We're not trying to be a global platform; we just want Denver to hang out.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Why not Facebook Groups?</summary>
        <p>Facebook's algorithm decides who sees what — events get buried, RSVPs don't actually mean "I'm coming," there's no capacity or waitlist, and conversations turn into chaos. Plus a lot of people don't want to be on Facebook. Here, every event has a real RSVP, a real host, and lands at the top of the page when it's posted. No algorithm.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Why not Discord?</summary>
        <p>Discord is great for chat. It's not great for "I'm coming Tuesday and so are 8 other people." Events get buried in channels, scheduled events are clunky, and there's no public discovery — people only see events if they're already in the server. We pair with Discord (you can sign in with it, link events to a Discord), but the event surface is here so anyone can find it.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Why not Sign Up Genius?</summary>
        <p>Sign Up Genius is a sign-up sheet. There's no profile, no community, no discovery, no level system, no waitlist that auto-promotes. It's perfect for "bring a casserole to the school bake sale." We have the sign-up part (potlucks even have claimable items, like SUG), but we also have everything around it — a real community surface where people actually find each other.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Why not Google Forms / Sheets?</summary>
        <p>Both are good for collecting answers. Neither helps strangers in Denver find your hike, RSVP, see who else is going, get a reminder, add it to their calendar, or build relationships across events. You'd end up DIY-building all of this and still have to share the spreadsheet link in 5 places. Hand-rolling community infrastructure is the project. We did it so you don't have to.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Why not Eventbrite or Partiful?</summary>
        <p>Eventbrite is built for ticketed events — concerts, conferences, festivals. Great at that, overkill for a coffee meetup. Partiful is beautiful for one-off parties (we drew some inspiration from it for the new event form), but each event is isolated. There's no community surface where you can find what's happening across Denver next week. Denver Social is the discovery layer.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>So what's the actual point?</summary>
        <p>One place to find real, in-person hangouts in Denver. No fees, no algorithms hiding your event, no app to download, no signup required to browse. Built specifically for the kind of small group where you'd actually remember someone's name afterward.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="hp-sec" id="attendees">
      <h2>For attendees</h2>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>How do I join an event?</summary>
        <p>Find one on <a href="/events">/events</a>, tap it, and hit RSVP. Most events need a free Discord or email sign-in so organizers know who's coming.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Do I need to bring anything?</summary>
        <p>It depends on the event. The event page tells you. Potlucks ask you to claim an item — pick whatever fits your kitchen.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>I RSVP'd. Can I cancel?</summary>
        <p>Yes — go to your <a href="/profile">profile</a>, find the event, hit Cancel. Please cancel early so the spot can go to someone on the waitlist.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Where are events held?</summary>
        <p>Across Denver — RiNo, Cap Hill, Cheesman, Cherry Creek, the foothills. Specific addresses are shared with confirmed RSVPs only.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>I can't see an event's full address.</summary>
        <p>You'll see it once you RSVP and (if the organizer set a gate) meet the karma/account-age minimum. Privacy keeps casual venues safe.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="hp-sec" id="groups">
      <h2>Groups</h2>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>What's a Group?</summary>
        <p>A smaller circle inside Denver Social — your hiking buddies, trivia crew, dinner club. Anyone can start one. Use them to post events scoped to that community instead of the whole site.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Public vs invite-only?</summary>
        <p>Public groups: anyone signed in can find them on <a href="/groups">/groups</a> and join freely. Invite-only: only people who get an invite link from a member can join.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>How do invites work?</summary>
        <p>Members can generate a one-time invite link from the group page. Anyone with that link can accept and join. Each link is single-use — once someone uses it, it's gone. Be careful sharing private-group links.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>How do I post an event in a group?</summary>
        <p>From the group page, hit "+ New event". The event you create gets tagged with the group, but it still shows up on the main events list (the group label is the only difference).</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>What if I want to leave a group?</summary>
        <p>Open the group, hit "Leave." If you're the owner and there are other members, you'll need to transfer ownership first (coming soon — for now, message us).</p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="hp-sec" id="organizers">
      <h2>For organizers</h2>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>How do I post an event?</summary>
        <p>Sign in, then go to <a href="/events/new">/events/new</a>. Pick a type, name it, pick a date on the calendar, fill in the details, post. Done.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Can I run a potluck?</summary>
        <p>Potluck-style sign-up sheets need approved-organizer access. <a href="/contact">Send us a message</a> and we'll flip your account on.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>How do I cap attendance?</summary>
        <p>Set a "spots" number when you post. Once it fills, new RSVPs go to a waitlist. If someone cancels, the top of the waitlist gets promoted automatically.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>How do reminders work?</summary>
        <p>Attendees get a reminder email the day before for potlucks. Standard events surface in the weekly digest if you have Resend configured.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>How do I delete an event?</summary>
        <p>Open the event and hit the red 🗑 Delete event button in the top-right. Wipes all RSVPs, comments, and bring-items. Cannot be undone.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>What if someone's a no-show?</summary>
        <p>Mark them as a no-show from your event's dashboard. Repeated no-shows lower a member's reliability score and gate them out of future capped events.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="hp-sec" id="privacy">
      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Who can see my email or phone?</summary>
        <p>Only the organizer of the event you signed up for. We don't share it across events and we don't sell anything to advertisers.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>How do I delete my account?</summary>
        <p>Sign in, go to <a href="/profile">/profile</a>, scroll to "Delete account". Removes your member record and any RSVPs.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="hp-sec" id="reporting">
      <h2>Reporting</h2>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>How do I report someone or something?</summary>
        <p>Every event page has a 🚩 Report button in the top-right. Group pages have one too (in the hero). Pick a reason, add a note, submit. Your report goes straight to admins.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>What happens after I report?</summary>
        <p>An admin reviews the report and either takes action (warning, content removed, account suspended) or dismisses it if it's a misunderstanding. We don't tell the reported person who flagged them.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>Do I need proof?</summary>
        <p>No. If someone makes you uncomfortable, that's reason enough to report. We err on the side of believing the person who spoke up.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="hp-q">
        <summary>What if it's an emergency?</summary>
        <p>Call 911. After you're safe, message us so we can act on our end.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="hp-sec" id="safety">
      <h2>Safety & terms</h2>
      <p class="hp-safety-intro">The short version.</p>

      <ol class="hp-rules">
        <li class="hp-rule">
          <span class="hp-rule-icon">👋</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Everyone's welcome.</strong>
            <p>Quiet, loud, awkward, neurodivergent, brand new to Denver — you're good here. Leave whenever. You don't owe anyone an explanation.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="hp-rule">
          <span class="hp-rule-icon">🔒</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Your info stays private.</strong>
            <p>Locations and host phone numbers are hidden until you RSVP. Other members only see your first name and neighborhood.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="hp-rule">
          <span class="hp-rule-icon">🎤</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Hosts are accountable.</strong>
            <p>Every event has a named host. Events get a quick moderation pass before going live. Groups stay small so things actually feel like a hangout.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="hp-rule hp-rule-warn">
          <span class="hp-rule-icon">🚫</span>
          <div>
            <strong>What gets you removed.</strong>
            <p>Harassment, intimidation, following someone after an event, or sharing someone's location or private info. You don't need proof to report — your word is enough.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="hp-rule">
          <span class="hp-rule-icon">📣</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Report anything that feels off.</strong>
            <p>Tell the host on the spot, jump in our Discord, or email us. We keep it between us.</p>
            <div class="hp-rule-btns">
              <a href="https://discord.gg/S8SFNkdSgK" class="hp-btn hp-btn-discord" target="_blank" rel="noopener">💬 Discord</a>
              <a href="/contact" class="hp-btn hp-btn-ghost">✉️ Contact us</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="hp-rule">
          <span class="hp-rule-icon">🎉</span>
          <div>
            <strong>It's free, and that's the deal.</strong>
            <p>No fees, no premium tier, no upsell. Some events have venue costs between you and the venue — we don't take a cut. Denver Social organizes the meetups but isn't liable for what happens at them.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <div class="hp-foot">
      Still stuck? <a href="/contact">Send us a message</a> or DM <code>@godtminilegs</code> on Discord.
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .hp-wrap { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px clamp(16px, 4vw, 40px) 80px; }
    .hp-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 28px; }
    .hp-header h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.025em; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .hp-sub { color: var(--text-sec); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.55; max-width: 540px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .hp-sub a { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }

    .hp-toc {
      display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; gap: 6px;
      padding: 12px; background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 999px; margin-bottom: 36px;
    }
    .hp-toc a {
      padding: 6px 14px; border-radius: 999px;
      font-family: var(--font); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-sec); text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
    }
    .hp-toc a:hover { background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); }

    .hp-sec { margin-bottom: 40px; scroll-margin-top: 96px; }
    .hp-sec h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 22px; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 14px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }

    .hp-q { background: var(--bg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); margin-bottom: 8px; overflow: hidden; }
    .hp-q summary { padding: 14px 16px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); cursor: pointer; list-style: none; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; }
    .hp-q summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
    .hp-q summary::after { content: '+'; color: var(--text-faint); font-size: 22px; font-weight: 400; flex-shrink: 0; }
    .hp-q[open] summary::after { content: '−'; }
    .hp-q[open] summary { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
    .hp-q p { padding: 12px 16px 16px; color: var(--text-sec); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; }
    .hp-q a { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
    .hp-why-intro { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-sec); margin-bottom: 12px; }

    /* Section lede + box grid */
    .hp-section-lede { font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-sec); line-height: 1.55; margin-bottom: 20px; max-width: 580px; }
    .hp-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; }
    .hp-box {
      padding: 18px 20px; background: var(--bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 16px;
      transition: transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
    }
    .hp-box:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); box-shadow: var(--card-shadow); }
    .hp-box-head { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .hp-box-head strong { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); }
    .hp-box-emoji { font-size: 22px; line-height: 1; }
    .hp-box p { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--text-sec); margin: 0; }
    .hp-box p strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 700; }
    .hp-box ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
    .hp-box ul li {
      font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-sec); line-height: 1.5;
      padding-left: 18px; position: relative;
    }
    .hp-box-ok ul li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--mint); font-weight: 800; }
    .hp-box-no ul li::before { content: '✕'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--sunset); font-weight: 800; }
    .hp-box-ok { background: linear-gradient(160deg, rgba(16,185,129,0.06), transparent); border-color: rgba(16,185,129,0.18); }
    .hp-box-no { background: linear-gradient(160deg, rgba(249,115,22,0.06), transparent); border-color: rgba(249,115,22,0.18); }
    .hp-box a { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
    .hp-box code { background: var(--surface); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 13px; }

    /* Safety rules */
    .hp-safety-intro { font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-sec); margin-bottom: 18px; }
    .hp-rules { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }
    .hp-rule {
      display: flex; gap: 16px; align-items: flex-start;
      padding: 18px clamp(16px, 3vw, 22px);
      background: var(--bg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 14px;
      transition: border-color 0.15s, transform 0.15s;
    }
    .hp-rule:hover { border-color: var(--border-hover); transform: translateY(-1px); }
    .hp-rule strong { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px; }
    .hp-rule p { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-sec); margin: 0; }
    .hp-rule-icon {
      flex-shrink: 0;
      width: 38px; height: 38px; border-radius: 50%;
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      font-size: 20px; background: var(--accent-dim);
    }
    .hp-rule-warn { background: linear-gradient(180deg, #FEF2F2, #fff); border-color: #FECACA; }
    .hp-rule-warn .hp-rule-icon { background: #FEE2E2; }
    .hp-rule-btns { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 12px; }
    .hp-btn {
      display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 999px;
      font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700;
      text-decoration: none; transition: transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
    }
    .hp-btn-discord { background: #5865F2; color: #fff; }
    .hp-btn-discord:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(88,101,242,0.3); }
    .hp-btn-ghost { background: var(--surface); color: var(--text); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
    .hp-btn-ghost:hover { background: var(--surface-hover); }

    .hp-foot { text-align: center; padding: 24px 16px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text-sec); font-size: 14px; margin-top: 32px; }
    .hp-foot a { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
    .hp-foot code { background: var(--surface); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 13px; }
  </style>
</Base>
